    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add the\u00a0<strong>linguine</strong>\u00a0to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain the linguine and reserve a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chorizo-and-spinach-linguine/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the linguine is cooking, peel and finely slice (don't chop!) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle\u00a0of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a\u00a0low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chorizo-and-spinach-linguine/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Turn the heat up to medium-high, add the <strong>diced chorizo</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until crisp</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chorizo-and-spinach-linguine/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chorizo is cooking, zest 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1] </span><strong>lemon </strong>(try to grate lightly with a micro-plane or sharp box grater and avoid grating the white pith, as this is very bitter)</p><p>Slice the <strong>remaining non-zested lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chorizo-and-spinach-linguine/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the chorizo is cooked, add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and 100ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [150ml]</span> <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> to the pan and cook for 2 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chorizo-and-spinach-linguine/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then add it to the pan along with the juice of the <strong>zested lemon </strong>(reserve the wedges for garnish)</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min further or until the spinach is wilted and you are left with a loose sauce</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemony-chorizo-and-spinach-linguine/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> to the pan and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>lemony chorizo & spinach linguine</strong></p>",
            "order": 7
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lemony chorizo & spinach linguine </strong>in shallow bowls and\u00a0top with the <strong>lemon zest</strong> and a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong> and garnish with a <strong>lemon wedge</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
